# Git workflow — work on `dev`, never commit to `main`

The repo has two long-lived branches:

- **`dev`** — ALL development happens here. Branch off `dev`, commit your work
  to `dev` (or to short-lived feature branches that merge back into `dev`), and
  push `dev`. This is the default working branch for everyone (humans and
  agents).
- **`main`** — host/production ONLY. It is what `typely.bauhub.online` runs
  (the GitHub Action `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` auto-deploys every push to
  `main` to the VPS). It must stay releasable at all times.

Hard rules:

1. Never commit or push directly to `main`.
2. `main` changes **only** through a **pull request from `dev`**, and **only**
   when the work is finished and tested ("cuando esté todo listo").
3. Before opening the PR, run `npm run build` (`tsc --noEmit && vite build`)
   and `npx tsc -p api/tsconfig.json` so `main` never breaks.
4. After each release, merge `main` back into `dev` so they don't drift.
5. The legacy `master` branch is historical — do not use it.
